post_text:
Is that an orange tomato? No, it's a persimmon, November's Harvest of the Month!

In Greek, the botanical name for persimmons is Diospyros, which means “fruit of the gods”. If you were one of the 2000+ students who tasted Fuyu persimmons today at school, you understand just how this delicious fall fruit got its name.

Fuyus can be eaten like an apple- crispy and sweet with hints of honey and vanilla- these bright orange fruits are a true seasonal treat. Robla students liked them so much that we just placed another order with @TerraFirmaFarm to include on next week's salad bars! #RoblaFamily #CaGrown #FarmtoSchool

post_text: Our Bell Avenue Elementary staff and students would like to thank the Sacramento Police Academy and Sacramento Police Department for orchestrating such a wonderful event for the second year in a row! This amazing event took place last Friday and included visits from the K-9 unit, motorcycles, mounted unit, and much more. We were even able to watch as Halo, the helicopter our sixth grade students helped to name in honor of officer Natalie Corona, landed on our field again! What an unforgettable Friday! post_text: Fresh fruits and vegetables on a warm spring day, what could be better?! Last week at Bell Avenue Elementary School, all of our students participated in a Farmers’ Market event that took place right on our own campus. The Farmers’ Market was a celebration for all of our Tigers who participated in the new Fresh Fruit and Vegetable Program this year. We know trying new things can be scary, but our Tigers have been fearless in our pursuit of obtaining healthier choices for them! We absolutely loved watching our students “shop” for their own fruits and vegetables and learn more about the bounty of local produce grown in the San Joaquin Valley. We are hoping that our Farmers’ Market event is something that we are able to expand to ALL Robla Sites next year! #RoblaFamily

post_text: Here in the Robla School District we know how important healthy meals are, which is why we strive to serve healthy choices at each and every one of our schools on a daily basis. Glenwood Elementary School, however, has taken our dedication to healthy choices to the next level by offering their parents a six week cooking class that focuses on creating healthy meals on a budget. At the end of each class, our participants are given a bag of groceries to take home and recreate the recipe they just learned. Would this be something you’d be interested in having at your campus? Leave us a comment below and let us know! #RoblaFamily

post_text: Our Bell Avenue Tigers and entire #RoblaFamily can’t thank the Sacramento Police Department enough for giving our students a once in a lifetime opportunity. Today, the new state-of-the-art Sacramento Police helicopter made its debut by landing on our Bell Avenue campus. What made an already incredible experience even more special was the name of the new helicopter, a name our sixth grade students came up with, Halo. This name was chosen specifically to honor fallen officer Natalie Corona who was loved greatly here at Bell Avenue. We will never forget this special day or the words that chief Hahn spoke, “This is YOUR helicopter!” Thank you again, Sacramento Police Department for all that you do for us and our community!
text: Our Bell Avenue Tigers and entire #RoblaFamily can’t thank the Sacramento Police Department enough for giving our students a once in a lifetime opportunity. Today, the new state-of-the-art Sacramento Police helicopter made its debut by landing on our Bell Avenue campus. What made an already incredible experience even more special was the name of the new helicopter, a name our sixth grade students came up with, Halo. This name was chosen specifically to honor fallen officer Natalie Corona who was loved greatly here at Bell Avenue. We will never forget this special day or the words that chief Hahn spoke, “This is YOUR helicopter!” Thank you again, Sacramento Police Department for all that you do for us and our community!

post_text: Thank you to the Sacramento Police Department for spreading holiday cheer in our community! Last week, one student from each school in the Robla School District, along with forty other students in surrounding areas, were selected for the Shop With a Cop event in which students are given a one hundred dollar Target gift card and are joined by friendly police officers while they shop. Our students absolutely loved spending time with the police officers! Thank you again, Sacramento Police Department for all you do for our community! #RoblaFamily
